This is a FastAPI project that includes authentication, chat functionality. The project uses SQLAlchemy for database operations and Pydantic for schema validation.

Requirements

Python 3.11
Install requirements from requirements.txt

Database

The project uses a SQLite database, and the database URL is set to sqlite:///./test.db.

Project Structure
The project is structured into the following directories:

app: contains the main application code


api: contains API routes for authentication and chat functionality
database: contains database models and database connection code

model: contains SQLAlchemy models

schemas: contains Pydantic schema definitions

websocket: contains WebSocket connection code

main.py: the main application file

How to Run
Install requirements from requirements.txt

Run  'uvicorn main:app --reload' to start / run the application

Use a tool like curl or a web browser to interact with the API
API Endpoints

auth

POST /auth/token: login and obtain an access token

POST /auth/signup: create a new user

Chat

POST /chat/messages: create a new message

GET /chat/messages/{conversationId}: get messages for a conversation





